"French Rococo Court":{"s":"The pastel-and-gold world of Madame de Pompadour's Versailles — powder-blue silk, panniers, and the last gasp of aristocratic excess before the Revolution.","e":"c.1720–1789, France","m":"Delicately excessive, pastel-dreaming, aristocratically sweet","g":["powder-blue silk robe à la française","wide pannier underskirt","towering powdered wig","silk mules"],"r":"Rare","a":["Marie Antoinette Aesthetic","Versailles Court","Rococo Pastoral"]},
